Evaluation
For this evaluation, n represents the number of courses stored in the data structure. The analysis focuses only on reading the file, checking file formatting, creating course objects, validating prerequisites, and inserting course objects into the data structure.
This analysis assumes that each course has a small, fixed number of prerequisites, as shown in the ABCU course data. Because prerequisites are stored as course numbers, the program must also check that every prerequisite listed exists as another course in the input file.

